<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>How do you know that your interpretation is the right one if you are not referring to the witness of the Holy Spirit telling you what is truth and what is not?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
By reason, logic, and by starting with fundamental Christian truths.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>In systematic theology doctrine must accord with doctrine. ...<br>
<br>
This law, while imperative, neither leads us away from the authority of Scripture nor lands us in a sphere of mere speculation.  All Christian doctrine, to be true, must be scriptural.  Doctrines in a system, to be true, must be accordant and scriptural.  If discordant or contradictory, some one or more must be both unscriptural and false.  Hence <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>this law of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>scientific</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> accordance in vitally related truths</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is consistent with the profoundest deference to the authority of revelation in all questions of Christian doctrine.<br>
<br>
This law may render valuable service in the construction and interpretation of Christian doctrine.  As we may interpret Scripture by Scripture, so may we interpret doctrine by doctrine.  Only, the interpreting doctrine must itself be certainly scriptural.  As such, no Christian doctrine can be out of accord with it.  In any distinction of standard or determining doctrines, preference should be given to the more fundamental; especially to such as are most certainly scriptural.<br>
<br>
John Miley, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The Atonement in Christ</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. (New York: Phillips and Hunt, 1879), 20-21.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brendamj>brendamj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#B87333>(8/9/03 3:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.northumbrian-lad.co.uk/HPIM0227.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Eugene<br>
